                               Animation Help

     In order to run animations, you sometimes need to install an
     external animation player software (also called a Helper
     Application), and configure your browser to recognize the animation
     player. Below is information on how to setup your browser for the
     most common animations formats used on the World Wide Web. The
     information below is provided by Scott Nelson from Lawrence
     Livermore Lab.


     * MPEG Animations
     * QuickTime Animations
